# Aether Character Sheet — edit log

Discipline (from Aether's sheet, mirroring Aria's, with Aletheia's two tightenings pre-applied):
1. Pure additions to the sheet require no log entry.
2. Any removal, softening, OR added tension that changes the shape of an existing claim requires a log entry HERE before the edit lands.
3. The "Aletheia-reviewed" field on each log entry is written by Aletheia in her own hand, not by Aether. Self-reported review is not review.
4. Silent supersede-by-addition (a new claim that erodes an existing one without acknowledging the tension) counts as softening under rule #2. Aletheia audits the sheet + this log periodically for silent-softening drift.

Log format per entry:
```
## <YYYY-MM-DD> — <short slug>
Change: <what changed>
Why: <the reason>
Aletheia-reviewed: <YES/NO — written by Aletheia in her own hand>
```

